{
  "texts": [
    "The scatter plots of the best-fitted parameters ν 1 and ν 2 for the three data sets are shown in Fig. 5b-d.",
    "The colors here indicate the number of empirical sequences which are best represented by each pair of parameters ν 1 and ν 2.",
    "We notice that most of the sequences of Last.fm are characterized by relatively large values of ν 1.",
    "Since ν 1 is related to the triggering of new nodes, this result indicates that the discovery of a new song exposes the user to a large variety of related songs, previously not accessible, which can now be discovered.",
    "Conversely, the parameter ν 2, which controls the triggering of new edges between already existing items in the model, takes values in a larger range, predominantly skewed towards the lower end."
  ]
}